# Local reference material and scratch assets -- deliberately NOT tracked.
#
# graphics/ holds third-party reference images (one is a watermarked Adobe
# Stock comp, one is Craiyon output). audio/ holds recordings captured from
# YouTube. Neither is licensed for redistribution, and a modified copy of a
# copyrighted recording is still a derivative work. Committing them would put
# them in git history permanently.
#
# Shipped audio must be either public domain / CC0 (with audio/CREDITS.md) or
# synthesized at runtime the way sound.py generates the chime.
graphics/
audio/
